1 (g) All of the information received by the State Board of Education through the checking
2 of the criminal history in accordance with this section is privileged information and is not a public
3 record but is for the exclusive and confidential use of the State Board and the governing board
4 of a public school unit considering employment of an individual granted licensure. The State
5 Board may destroy the information used for the purposes authorized by this section after the
6 licensure of the individual has ended or has been renewed. The governing body of a public school
