16 set forth in Article 31 of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes.
17 (i) Any applicant for licensure who willfully furnishes, supplies, or otherwise gives false
18 information on a licensure application that is the basis for a criminal history record check under
19 this section shall be guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor."
20 SECTION 2.(e) The State Board of Education is encouraged to work toward
21 programming the licensure system to align with the Multistate Educator Lookup System
22 established by the National Association of State Directors of Teacher Education and Certification
23 to enable electronic validation of out-of-state credentials and related information.
24 SECTION 2.(f) This section applies to applications for licensure that are received
25 on or after October 1, 2025.
