27 PART III. CRIMINAL HISTORY CHECKS FOR PUBLIC SCHOOL UNIT
28 PERSONNEL
29 SECTION 3.(a) There is established in Article 7B of Chapter 115C of the General
30 Statutes a new Part to read "Part 7. Public School Unit Personnel."
31 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 115C-332 is recodified into Part 7 of Article 7B of Chapter
32 115C of the General Statutes, as established by this act, as G.S. 115C-77 and reads as rewritten:
33 "§ 115C-77. School personnel criminal history checks.
34 (a) As used The following definitions apply in this section:
35 (1) "Criminal history" means a Criminal history. – A county, state, or federal
36 criminal history of conviction of a crime, whether a misdemeanor or a felony,
37 that indicates the employee (i) poses a threat to the physical safety of students
38 or personnel, or (ii) has demonstrated that he or she does not have the integrity
39 or honesty to fulfill his or her duties as public school personnel. Such crimes
40 include the following North Carolina crimes contained in any of the following
41 Articles of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes: Article 5A, Endangering
42 Executive and Legislative Executive, Legislative, and Court Officers; Article
43 6, Homicide; Article 7B, Rape and Kindred Other Sex Offenses; Article 8,
44 Assaults; Article 10, Kidnapping and Abduction; Article 13, Malicious Injury
45 or Damage by Use of Explosive or Incendiary Device or Material; Article 14,
46 Burglary and Other Housebreakings; Article 15, Arson and Other Burnings;
47 Article 16, Larceny; Article 17, Robbery; Article 18, Embezzlement; Article
48 19, False Pretense and Cheats; Article 19A, Obtaining Property or Services
49 by False or Fraudulent Use of Credit Device or Other Means; Article 20,
50 Frauds; Article 21, Forgery; Article 26, Offenses Against Public Morality and
51 Decency; Article 26A, Adult Establishments; Article 27, Prostitution; Article
Page 4 House Bill 775-First Edition

