38 (e) State Board of Education to Receive Copy. – The local board of education, governing
39 body, or the superintendent or equivalent authority, if designated by the local board of education,
40 shall provide to the State Board of Education the criminal history it receives on a person who is
41 certificated, certified, or licensed by the State Board of Education. The State Board of Education
42 shall review the criminal history and determine whether the person's certificate or license should
43 be revoked in accordance with State laws and rules regarding revocation.
44 (f) Criminal History Check Documents Not Public Record. – All the information
45 received by the local board of education through the checking of the criminal history or by a
46 governing body or the State Board of Education in accordance with this section is privileged
47 information and is not a public record but is for the exclusive use of the local board of education
